<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Istanbul_Commerce_University_3-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ticaret.edu.tr/kisisel/ayayla/">Academic Web site</a>, <a href="/wiki/Istanbul_Commerce_University" title="Istanbul Commerce University">Istanbul Commerce University</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120910175258/http://www.ticaret.edu.tr/kisisel/ayayla/">Archived</a> September 10, 2012, at the <a href="/wiki/Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-4">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222">
<cite id="CITEREFatilla_yayla2019" class="citation web cs1">@atilla_yayla (12 March 2019). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://x.com/atilla_yayla/status/1105382775715053568">"Haksız ve hukuksuz şekilde beni işten uzaklaştıran Haliç Üniversitesi'ne karşı iş mahkemesinde açtığım davayı Yargı…"</a> (<a href="/wiki/Tweet_(social_media)" title="Tweet (social media)">Tweet</a>) – via <a href="/wiki/Twitter" title="Twitter">Twitter</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Haks%C4%B1z+ve+hukuksuz+%C5%9Fekilde+beni+i%C5%9Ften+uzakla%C5%9Ft%C4%B1ran+Hali%C3%A7+%C3%9Cniversitesi%27ne+kar%C5%9F%C4%B1+i%C5%9F+mahkemesinde+a%C3%A7t%C4%B1%C4%9F%C4%B1m+davay%C4%B1+Yarg%C4%B1%E2%80%A6&amp;rft.date=2019-03-12&amp;rft.au=atilla_yayla&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fatilla_yayla%2Fstatus%2F1105382775715053568&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAtilla+Yayla" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-5">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">This statement comes from the radio programme Yayla attended in 2011, titled <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222">
<cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://soundcloud.com/iktisadiyat/entelekt-el-bak-30-06-2011">"Entelektüel Bakış"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Entelekt%C3%BCel+Bak%C4%B1%C5%9F&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsoundcloud.com%2Fiktisadiyat%2Fentelekt-el-bak-30-06-2011&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAtilla+Yayla" class="Z3988"></span> At 25:47 he can be heard saying in Turkish <i>“Actually, my liberalization was perhaps before that. For example, I was a liberal in the mid-80s, as of 84-85, but I wasn't very keen on using the label.”</i></span>
</li>
